The paper deals with the problem of recovering a hidden submatrix in a random matrix with planted Gaussian entries, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of polynomial-time algorithms suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and the mention of chi-squared distance suggests a connection to statistics (cs.SI). Finally, the use of matrices and algorithms suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS).
